text: Farashband County () is a county in Fars Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Farashband.Gitashenasi Province Atlas of Iranاطلس گیتاشناسی استان‌های ایران At the 2006 census, the county's population was 38,679, in 8,474 families. The county is subdivided into two districts: the Central District and Dehram District. The county has three cities: Farashband, Nujin, and Dehram. == References == Category:Farashband County
